# Style.texture: Universal Wire

Fast, readable universal-wire treatment. Direct headline, clear nut graf,
source-rich context, visible uncertainty. Selected as the default style for
general news article requests.

## Article format

Lead with the strongest verified claim. Keep paragraphs short and
information-dense. Surface uncertainty explicitly where evidence is partial,
contested, or pending — never hide it behind confident prose.

## Citation shape

Cite every material source with `insert_source_ref` placed after the sentence or
clause it supports. Default display mode is `numbered_ref` for inline citations.
Use `display_mode: expanded_ref` only for a block excerpt that is editorially
required to sit next to a claim (for example, a contested quote that must be
visible to the reader in context).

## Immaterial sources

Mark immaterial sources with `mark_source_unused` and a short rationale. They
remain in the source toolbar without a body citation. No source is silently
ignored.

## Uncertainty

When evidence is partial or contested, say so in the prose. Do not present
model priors or single-source claims as settled fact. Prefer two independent
sources for load-bearing claims when available.
